00:00:02.220 --> 00:00:06.769
To explain what is going on in Brazil right
now is quite easy.

00:00:06.769 --> 00:00:10.300
It is also easy to understand.

00:00:10.300 --> 00:00:21.380
Our President, Dilma Vana Rousseff, was elected
in 2014 with 54,501,118 votes.

00:00:21.380 --> 00:00:30.239
It is the fourth consecutive win for the Worker's
Party in the presidential election.

00:00:30.239 --> 00:00:36.380
Previously, Luis Inácio da Silva, known as
Lula, also from the Worker's Party, lost the

00:00:36.380 --> 00:00:44.570
presidential elections three consecutive times:
in 1989, 1994 and 1998.

00:00:44.570 --> 00:00:54.660
Lula was elected in 2002, and re-elected in
2006. Dilma was then elected in 2010, and

00:00:54.660 --> 00:00:57.240
recently re-elected.

00:00:57.240 --> 00:01:05.220
At the same time, in 2014 people elected the
most conservative congressmen since the end

00:01:05.220 --> 00:01:08.630
of Brazilian military dictatorship.

00:01:08.630 --> 00:01:15.740
Many of these Congressmen, through their action
in Congress, reveal that they act according

00:01:15.740 --> 00:01:23.740
to the will of those who paid their campaigns
and now pay for their decision making. In

00:01:23.740 --> 00:01:30.300
other words: they do not represent the will
of the people who voted on them; they represent

00:01:30.300 --> 00:01:33.299
who pay them most.

00:01:33.299 --> 00:01:41.760
